  "prompt": "What happened to Mt. Gox?",
  "response": "Mt. Gox was once the largest Bitcoin exchange in the world. In 2014, it collapsed after approximately 850,000 bitcoins (worth around $450 million at the time) were stolen through a massive hack. The exchange filed for bankruptcy in Tokyo, and its CEO Mark Karpel\u00e8s was later charged with fraud and embezzlement. In 2018, a rehabilitation process began to try to return some funds to creditors, but many users never recovered their lost cryptocurrency. The Mt. Gox incident is considered one of the most significant early disasters in Bitcoin's history and highlighted the security risks in cryptocurrency exchanges.",
